Package: dosefitr
Title: Dose-Response Curve Fitting for NanoBRET and Cell Viability Assays
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Thiago", "Loreto Matos", 
           email = "thiago-loreto@hotmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Thiago Loreto Matos <thiago-loreto@hotmail.com>
Description: 
    End-to-end dose-response analysis pipeline for NanoBRET kinase binding
    assays and cell viability experiments. Reads raw BMG PHERAstar plate-reader
    exports, computes BRET ratios, detects and removes outliers (ROUT method),
    and fits three- or four-parameter logistic models to derive IC50 and pIC50
    values with confidence intervals. Provides automatic quality control metrics
    (Z-prime, assay window, signal-to-background, CV%), batch processing across
    multiple plates, outlier visualisation, multi-compound overlay plots, and
    plate-comparison plots. Exports results to Excel and generates
    Scarab-formatted tables for NanoBRET kinase profiling data submission.
